# Force LF line endings for files where byte-for-byte content matters.
#
# Windows-side `git config core.autocrlf=true` would otherwise rewrite checked-in
# `\n` to `\r\n` at checkout time, which breaks:
#   - gofmt / golangci-lint, which are LF-only (Windows CI lint job fails otherwise)
#   - shell scripts run via `bash` on macOS/Linux
#   - YAML / JSON manifests generated and compared
#
# These rules ensure every contributor and CI runner sees the canonical LF form.

# Shell scripts.
*.sh text eol=lf

# CI / compose YAML.
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# Go source files (gofmt is LF-only anyway, but be explicit).
*.go text eol=lf

# Markdown (so cross-OS reviews don't see noise).
*.md text eol=lf

# Default: let git auto-detect; binaries are unaffected.
* text=auto
